<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7159> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7159" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 129 (no. 9 in the consilium listed in the SC de agro Pergameno in copy B, no. 24 in copy A). See Sherk, RDGE no. 12, pp. 63-73. The praenomen of the father of no. 5 appears in the text tradition of Josephus as # possibly a corruption of Cnaeus, but this praenomen is improbable since the Sempronii of the Republic do not use it. More probably these two Sempronii may be identified. As none of the known Gracchi or Tuditani of the period appear to fit, he may be a Sempronius Longus, son of the Xvir s. f. of 174 (no. 63; MRR 1.406), and father of the legatus of ca. 96 (no. 64; MRR 2.10). But on the date, see above, on M'. Aquillius (10).\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7159 .
